                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.584/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Sweden (<persName type="to">Morehead</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-07T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 7, 1933—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. Your despatch 620, December 6, 1932. You are authorized to sign convention
                    limited to military obligations. See page 3, lines 3 to 7, Department’s
                    instruction No. 73, September 2, 1931. Full powers by early pouch.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
